confirmed as successor of his <a href="/nepal/words/viewitem/2199">guru</a> <a href="/nepal/ontologies/viewitem/284">Jagadīśvaranātha</a> by Lieutenant General <a href="/nepal/ontologies/viewitem/185">Vīra Śamśera Jaṅga Bahādura Rāṇā</a> in VS 1878 (VS 1935 Śrāvaṇa vadi 14; K_0097_0040) and by King <a href="/nepal/ontologies/viewitem/356">Pṛthvī</a> in 1882 (VS 1938 Phālguna vadi 2; K_0469_0001);
</p>
involved in a conflict with <a href="/nepal/ontologies/viewitem/382">Haṃsanātha</a> (who accused him of debauchery) that was solved by Prime Minister <a href="/nepal/ontologies/viewitem/100">Raṇa Uddīpa Siṃha Kũvara Rāṇā</a> and led to a splitting of the office of the <a href="/nepal/words/viewitem/1805">maṇḍalāi</a> and the related revenues in 1883 (cf. <a href="/nepal/books/viewitem/92">Naraharinātha VS 2022</a>: 456f.; <a href="/nepal/books/viewitem/108">Bouillier 1991</a>: 166 and <a href="/nepal/books/viewitem/454">Zotter 2018</a>: 455f.);
