<p/>
details: 
<p/>
first successor of <a href="/nepal/ontologies/viewitem/1">Bhagavantanātha</a> on the throne (<a href="/nepal/words/viewitem/2324">gaddī</a>) in <a href="/nepal/ontologies/viewitem/3">Rānāgāũ</a>; 
</p>
in 1787 (VS 1844) King <a href="/nepal/ontologies/viewitem/177">Raṇabahādura</a> wrote a letter addressing the thrice venerable (<i/>śrī 3</i>) Bhuvaneśvaranātha as "<i/>śrīmad gorakṣapraṇītāgamadharmānuṣṭhānaparāyaṇa</i>" (<a href="/nepal/books/viewitem/92">Naraharinātha VS 2022</a>: 459; cf. <a href="/nepal/books/viewitem/108">Bouillier 1991</a>: 159)
</p>
in 1790 (VS 1847), he built the <a href="/nepal/words/viewitem/2454">samādhi</a> of <a href="/nepal/ontologies/viewitem/1/1">Bhagavantanātha</a> in <a href="/nepal/ontologies/viewitem/390">Śrīgāũ</a> (<a href="/nepal/books/viewitem/110">Unbescheid 1980</a>: 28 [with reference to Yogīvaṃśāvalī II, p. 89; cf. <a href="/nepal/books/viewitem/108">Bouillier 1991</a>: 159);
</p>
in 1797 (VS 1854), he received an executive order of <a href="/nepal/ontologies/viewitem/286">Raṇabhīma Śāha</a> confirming  a <a href="/nepal/words/viewitem/891">birtā</a> grant originally given to <a href="/nepal/ontologies/viewitem/1">Bhagavantanātha</a> by Raṇabhīma's father, <a href="/nepal/ontologies/viewitem/381">Śrīkṛṣṇa Śāha</a>, the king of <a href="/nepal/ontologies/viewitem/6">Salyan</a> (<a href="/nepal/books/viewitem/92">Naraharinātha VS 2022</a>: 460; for copies, see <a href="/nepal/editions/show/42412">K_0123_0050</a> and <a href="/nepal/editions/show/45898">K_0469_0025</a>, see also the summary in K_0469_0017 [doc. 7]);
<p/>
as Bouillier writes his <a href="/nepal/words/viewitem/1806">mahanta</a>-ships lasted almost thirty years (<a href="/nepal/books/viewitem/108">1991</a>: 160);
</p>
suceeded by his disciple <a href="/nepal/ontologies/viewitem/287">Rūpanātha</a>. 
