also known as: Bhavānibhakta Siṃ Khatrī, Bhawani Singh Khatri (?);
<p/>
flourished: 1832;
<p/>
gender: male;
<p/>
details:
<p/>
held the title of <a href="/nepal/words/viewitem/2542">lephṭena</a> (1832, DNA_0002_0016);
<p/>
remarks: 
<p/>
A person called Bhawani Singh Khatri is attested in the secondary literature. <a href="/nepal/books/viewitem/913">Vaidya and Manandhar 1985</a>: 149 refer to a letter on judicial a matter from Bhīmasena Thāpā to a certain Lieutenant Bhawani Singh Khatri dated 1830. <a href="/nepal/books/viewitem/81">Whelpton 1991</a>: 181 n.53 reports of a <a href="/nepal/words/viewitem/1098">sardāra</a> Bhawani Singh as one of the aides of Māthavara Siṃ Thāpa in 1844. <a href="/nepal/books/viewitem/81">Whelpton 1991</a>: 136 further mentions that this Bhawanī Singh Khatri fled to India together with Abhimāna Siṃ Basnyāt in 1845. He was killed shortly after the Kot Massacre of 1846 (<a href="/nepal/books/viewitem/81">Whelpton 1991</a>: 163). However, it cannot be determined with certainty that both persons are the same;
<p/>
probably <a href="/nepal/ontologies/viewitem/1827">Bhavānibhakta Khatṛ</a> is still another person.
#checked#

