<p/>
the first reference to "Khaḍagakoṭ" is found in a <a href="/nepal/words/viewitem/358">syāhāmohara</a> of <a href="/nepal/ontologies/viewitem/381">Śrīkṛṣṇa Śāha</a> granting <a href="/nepal/ontologies/viewitem/1">Bhagavantanātha</a> different revenues (such as the forest tax) in 1776/77 (VS 1833, see summary in K_0469_0017 [doc. 6]);
<p/>
a <a href="/nepal/words/viewitem/358">syāhāmohara</a> of <a href="/nepal/ontologies/viewitem/381">Śrīkṛṣṇa Śāha</a>, issued in 1781 (ŚS 1702), mentions that <a href="/nepal/ontologies/viewitem/1">Bhagavantanātha</a> received "<a href="/nepal/ontologies/viewitem/400">Pedā</a> of Kharkākoṭa" (<a href="/nepal/books/viewitem/92">Naraharinātha VS 2022</a>: 459) / "° Khaḍagākoṭ" (K_0469_0017 [doc. 12]); Bouillier discussing this document suggests that Kharkākoṭa is another name of <a href="/nepal/ontologies/viewitem/390">Śrīgāũ</a> (<a href="/nepal/books/viewitem/80">Bouillier 1991</a>: 13), table 21 in K_0469_0017 lists "Kharkākoṭ together with Pedā" under the heading "[<a href="/nepal/words/viewitem/1898">birtā</a>s] in Dang";
<p/>
a <a href="/nepal/words/viewitem/992">lālāmohara</a> of King <a href="/nepal/ontologies/viewitem/140">Rājendra</a> issued in the name of <a href="/nepal/ontologies/viewitem/287">Rūpanātha</a> in 1820 (VS 1877) mentions  "Khaḍkākoṭa"(K_0469_0018) / "Khaḍkā Koṭ" (<a href="/nepal/books/viewitem/92">Naraharinātha VS 2022</a>: 461) / "Khaḍagākoṭ" (K_0469_0017 [doc. 4]) as one of the confirmed <a href="/nepal/words/viewitem/1898">birtā</a>s in <a href="/nepal/ontologies/viewitem/392">Deukhuri</a>;
