details:
<p/>
famous court astrologer;
<p/>
came to Kathmandu around 1778;
<p/>
joined the conquests of western Nepal under <a href="/nepal/ontologies/viewitem/229">Bahādura Śāha</a>; 
<p/>
kept track of military events in his almanac and fixed the auspicious timings for the attacks when the Gorkhālīs conquered some <a href="/nepal/ontologies/viewitem/628">Bāīse Rājya</a>s and <a href="/nepal/ontologies/viewitem/589">Caubīsī Rājya</a>s in 1786;
<p/>
wrote the Durgārcanakalpataru for Raṇabhīma Śāha of Salyan in 1793; 
<p/>
spent his last years at Varanasi;
